<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 14:04:46 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>全向海胆状机器人挑战传统设计</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/omnidirectional-sea-urchin-like-robot-defies-traditional-designs</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 14:04:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/omnidirectional-sea-urchin-like-robot-defies-traditional-designs</guid></item><item><title>“粉红噪音”有助于手术期间麻醉效果更好</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/pink-noise-can-help-make-anesthesia-work-better-during-surgery</link><description>在大脑中，特定的电波与不同的意识状态相关。例如，δ波（也称为慢波）在深度睡眠期间以及昏迷和全身麻醉引起的无意识状态期间尤其普遍。它们被认为是这些改变的意识状态的“签名”。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/pink-noise-can-help-make-anesthesia-work-better-during-surgery.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 13:49:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/pink-noise-can-help-make-anesthesia-work-better-during-surgery</guid></item><item><title>生物标志物可以帮助识别有慢性危重疾病风险的 ICU 患者</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/biomarkers-could-help-identify-icu-patients-at-risk-of-chronic-critical-illness</link><description>新研究，发表于&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/biomarkers-could-help-identify-icu-patients-at-risk-of-chronic-critical-illness.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 13:34:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/biomarkers-could-help-identify-icu-patients-at-risk-of-chronic-critical-illness</guid></item><item><title>人工智能系统设计假设和测试它们的方法</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/ai-systems-devise-hypotheses-and-ways-to-test-them</link><description>人工智能代理协作生成生物医学假设并分析数据，迈向实验室发现周期，人工智能参与每一步。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ai-systems-devise-hypotheses-and-ways-to-test-them2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 13:19:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/ai-systems-devise-hypotheses-and-ways-to-test-them</guid></item><item><title>科学家们找到了如何缩小巨大的超快激光器，使其安装在一个微小的芯片上——该领域的“圣杯”</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/scientists-figured-out-how-to-shrink-huge-ultrafast-lasers-so-they-fit-on-a-tiny-chip-the-holy-grail-of-the-field</link><description>科学家们已经成功地让超快激光器在微型芯片上运行，为微型但功能强大的诊断设备铺平了道路。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/scientists-figured-out-how-to-shrink-huge-ultrafast-lasers-so-they-fit-on-a-tiny-chip-the-holy-grail-of-the-field.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 13:04:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/scientists-figured-out-how-to-shrink-huge-ultrafast-lasers-so-they-fit-on-a-tiny-chip-the-holy-grail-of-the-field</guid></item><item><title>科学家只发现了现存昆虫物种的一小部分</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/scientists-have-only-discovered-a-tiny-fraction-of-living-insect-species</link><description>大约有 100 万种昆虫已被描述，但一项新的分析表明可能还有数千万种昆虫&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/scientists-have-only-discovered-a-tiny-fraction-of-living-insect-species2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 12:49:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/scientists-have-only-discovered-a-tiny-fraction-of-living-insect-species</guid></item><item><title>错误信息利用愤怒在网上传播</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/misinformation-exploits-outrage-to-spread-online</link><description>我们测试了一个假设，即错误信息利用愤怒在网上传播，检验了跨多个平台、时间段和错误信息分类的普遍性。愤怒具有很强的吸引力，并且不需要准确地实现其沟通目标，这使其成为嵌入错误信息的有吸引力的信号。在使用来自 Facebook（1,063,298 个链接）和 Twitter（44,529 条推文，24,007 位用户）的美国数据以及两项行为实验（1475 名参与者）的八项研究中，我们表明：(i) 错误信息来源比可信来源更能引起愤怒； (ii) 愤怒至少与分享可信新闻一样强烈地促进了错误信息的传播； (iii) 用户更愿意在不先阅读的情况下分享引发愤怒的错误信息。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/misinformation-exploits-outrage-to-spread-online2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 12:34:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/misinformation-exploits-outrage-to-spread-online</guid></item><item><title>利益冲突</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/conflict-of-interest</link><description>地址通信至：Puneet Opal，Denning Ataxia Center，Department of Neurology，Northwestern Feinberg School of Medicine，Ward 10-332303 East Chicago Avenue，Chicago，Illinois 69,611，USA。电话：312.503.4699；电子邮件：&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/conflict-of-interest.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 12:19:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/conflict-of-interest</guid></item><item><title>AARS1 通过 ATF6 乳酰化介导的肝细胞癌色氨酸代谢促进肿瘤进展和免疫逃避</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/aars1-promotes-tumor-progression-and-immune-evasion-via-atf6-lactylation-mediated-tryptophan-metabolism-in-hepatocellular-carcinoma</link><description>王等人。确定了肝细胞癌中的代谢免疫反馈回路，其中肿瘤细胞固有的 AARS1 介导的 ATF6 乳酰化激活 TDO2-犬尿氨酸轴以促进 Treg 分化和免疫抑制，而 Treg 衍生的 eNAMPT 增强肿瘤糖酵解和乳酸产生，揭示了对 AARS1 抑制与 PD-1/PD-L1 阻断相结合的治疗脆弱性。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/aars1-promotes-tumor-progression-and-immune-evasion-via-atf6-lactylation-mediated-tryptophan-metabolism-in-hepatocellular-carcinoma.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 12:04:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/aars1-promotes-tumor-progression-and-immune-evasion-via-atf6-lactylation-mediated-tryptophan-metabolism-in-hepatocellular-carcinoma</guid></item><item><title>丛枝菌根真菌网络的整体密度和生物量</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/global-density-and-biomass-of-arbuscular-mycorrhizal-fungal-networks</link><description>丛枝菌根真菌与约 70% 的植物物种形成共生，构建菌丝网络，以交换宿主来源的碳的养分。这些管状网络每年将约 10 亿吨碳转移到地球土壤中。然而，我们对进行这种资源转移所需的菌丝基础设施没有定量的了解。我们收集了来自 322 项研究的数据，这些研究代表了九个生物群落的 16,000 多个土壤核心，并开发了机器学习模型来预测全球菌丝密度。通过机器人对超过 300,000 个菌丝进行成像，我们根据空间预测校准了生物量模型。我们估计全球表土含有 1.10 × 10 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/global-density-and-biomass-of-arbuscular-mycorrhizal-fungal-networks2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 11:49:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/global-density-and-biomass-of-arbuscular-mycorrhizal-fungal-networks</guid></item></channel></rss>